WEBVTT

00:00:34.722 --> 00:00:38.059
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

00:00:42.480 --> 00:00:44.649
You can call her big sis.

00:00:44.732 --> 00:00:46.276
Everyone knows she's old.

00:00:52.365 --> 00:00:54.450
Well, we know.

00:01:03.710 --> 00:01:04.794
I'm sorry.

00:01:10.049 --> 00:01:11.217
Mommy!

00:01:12.510 --> 00:01:13.344
Bom?

00:01:15.805 --> 00:01:16.639
Bom.

00:01:18.099 --> 00:01:18.933
Bom!

00:01:25.023 --> 00:01:26.441
Bom, I'm so sorry.

00:01:41.414 --> 00:01:42.457
What?

00:01:43.207 --> 00:01:44.083
Hong Jang-mi?

00:01:44.167 --> 00:01:46.628
The slush fund hidden under her name

00:01:47.587 --> 00:01:48.630
has all been withdrawn.

00:01:49.714 --> 00:01:53.134
Are you saying
she went in person to withdraw it?

00:01:53.218 --> 00:01:54.052
Yes.

00:01:54.135 --> 00:01:57.805
The branch manager said
she had an authorization letter

00:01:58.389 --> 00:01:59.807
and that he even spoke to you.

00:02:02.268 --> 00:02:03.144
Also,

00:02:03.686 --> 00:02:07.482
all three financial institutions
in Chungseo were looted.

00:02:11.861 --> 00:02:14.364
Bring the branch manager of Saenara Bank
to Seoul right now.

00:02:16.366 --> 00:02:17.242
All right.

00:02:31.798 --> 00:02:33.341
EMPLOYEE PERSONNEL RECORD

00:02:33.424 --> 00:02:34.509
Hong Jang-mi.

00:02:35.260 --> 00:02:36.469
You've got some nerve.

00:02:38.346 --> 00:02:40.390
How dare you touch that 24 billion won?

00:03:02.745 --> 00:03:05.707
You guys are secretly planning something,
aren't you?

00:03:07.959 --> 00:03:09.502
What do you mean?

00:03:15.550 --> 00:03:17.802
Can I come with you to the dorms?

00:03:17.885 --> 00:03:20.179
I still have some stuff there
that I need to pick up.

00:03:20.263 --> 00:03:22.390
I already called the RA
and got her permission.

00:03:22.473 --> 00:03:23.599
I figured I could go today…

00:03:23.683 --> 00:03:25.560
No. You can't.

00:03:25.643 --> 00:03:27.562
Tell me what you need,
and I'll send them to you.

00:03:29.814 --> 00:03:31.441
There really is something you're hiding.

00:03:32.817 --> 00:03:35.194
Come on, what is it?
Don't leave me out again.

00:03:37.113 --> 00:03:39.157
I think we can tell Ms. Kang, no?

00:03:39.741 --> 00:03:40.992
I mean, Big Al knows too.

00:03:41.075 --> 00:03:42.201
No.

00:03:42.285 --> 00:03:44.037
She's way further up the family tree.

00:03:45.455 --> 00:03:46.331
Albert knows?

00:03:46.831 --> 00:03:49.584
Why won't you tell me when even he knows?

00:04:23.576 --> 00:04:24.577
Hey, you…

00:04:34.379 --> 00:04:36.964
Thank you for coming
all this way to Seoul.

00:04:37.048 --> 00:04:38.508
I needed to confirm something with you.

00:04:40.885 --> 00:04:42.261
Was it her who withdrew the money?

00:04:45.264 --> 00:04:47.392
Yes, it was her.

00:04:47.475 --> 00:04:48.559
Hong Jang-mi.

00:04:48.643 --> 00:04:50.603
She came and withdrew it in person.

00:04:51.187 --> 00:04:54.023
Ms. Song, we spoke
on the phone then, remember?

00:04:54.607 --> 00:04:55.983
That wasn't me.

00:04:56.776 --> 00:04:57.610
Pardon?

00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:08.413
This is Hong Jang-mi?

00:05:09.622 --> 00:05:11.749
Are you sure it's not Hong Keum-bo?

00:05:27.014 --> 00:05:28.558
That shell company

00:05:29.142 --> 00:05:31.477
buying up the Hanmin bonds
you mentioned last time.

00:05:32.186 --> 00:05:35.106
I confirmed
it was being funded by DK Ventures.

00:05:36.441 --> 00:05:37.442
We expected as much.

00:05:38.401 --> 00:05:41.279
It's not too late
to let them handle it on their own.

00:05:41.988 --> 00:05:44.991
I'm sure if Chairman Kang knew
what DK Ventures was scheming,

00:05:45.074 --> 00:05:46.742
he'd figure something out.

00:05:46.826 --> 00:05:48.369
Are you telling me to back out?

00:05:48.452 --> 00:05:49.787
No.

00:05:50.705 --> 00:05:54.208
I'm just saying we should give
Chairman Kang Pil-beom a chance

00:05:54.292 --> 00:05:55.793
to save Hanmin through his own efforts.

00:05:55.877 --> 00:05:59.297
The privileged get
all the second chances in this world,

00:06:00.047 --> 00:06:02.216
while the rest get only one shot.

00:06:02.300 --> 00:06:04.510
I'm just worried
about the dangers you'll face.

00:06:05.094 --> 00:06:07.013
I believe this will be my last chance.

00:06:08.222 --> 00:06:10.016
I'm going to start by knocking down

00:06:10.600 --> 00:06:12.059
Chairman Kang's pawns one by one.

00:06:24.488 --> 00:06:26.532
EPISODE 13: WITCH HUNT

00:06:27.783 --> 00:06:28.993
Hong Jang-mi.

00:06:30.912 --> 00:06:32.538
{\an8}When are you going to grow up?

00:06:32.622 --> 00:06:33.831
{\an8}ULLALA CHICKEN

00:06:33.915 --> 00:06:35.875
{\an8}Hey, we have a customer. Welcome!

00:06:35.958 --> 00:06:37.376
{\an8}We have a customer. Welcome, sir.

00:06:37.460 --> 00:06:38.878
{\an8}Have a seat wherever you'd like.

00:06:41.214 --> 00:06:42.673
{\an8}What would you like to order?

00:06:43.966 --> 00:06:47.178
{\an8}Can I get a fried chicken and a soda?

00:06:47.261 --> 00:06:48.846
{\an8}- Yes, sure. It'll be right up.
- Thanks.

00:06:49.972 --> 00:06:54.227
{\an8}Your sister spent all that money on you
for that boarding cram school.

00:06:54.310 --> 00:06:56.771
{\an8}The least you can do is study
as if your life depended on it,

00:06:56.854 --> 00:06:57.897
{\an8}not run away!

00:06:57.980 --> 00:07:00.316
{\an8}I just don't have the brains for it.

00:07:00.399 --> 00:07:01.984
{\an8}I'm not cut out for school.

00:07:02.568 --> 00:07:05.196
And you just don't know
what that place is like.

00:07:05.279 --> 00:07:07.114
Even Keum-bo
wouldn't be able to last there.

00:07:09.492 --> 00:07:11.452
How can sisters be such polar opposites?

00:07:11.535 --> 00:07:13.162
I, Hong Jang-mi,

00:07:13.246 --> 00:07:15.873
can never be like Hong Keum-bo.

00:07:15.957 --> 00:07:17.583
Just give up already, Mom.

00:07:17.667 --> 00:07:18.960
Where do you think you're going?

00:07:19.043 --> 00:07:20.586
- Get back here!
- Stop it.

00:07:23.923 --> 00:07:25.258
I'm sorry about all that.

00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:27.385
She must be your youngest daughter.

00:07:27.468 --> 00:07:29.971
Yes, we have two princesses.

00:07:30.888 --> 00:07:33.057
That's our youngest,
and the eldest works in Yeouido.

00:07:33.140 --> 00:07:34.350
Yeouido?

00:07:35.476 --> 00:07:36.978
You must be so proud of her.

00:07:39.021 --> 00:07:40.189
Yes, I am.

00:07:40.273 --> 00:07:41.816
- Just give me a moment.
- Sure.

00:07:43.818 --> 00:07:44.652
Go.

00:07:57.331 --> 00:08:01.210
We need to reallocate the slush fund.

00:08:04.338 --> 00:08:06.132
Do you mean fund rebalancing?

00:08:06.215 --> 00:08:08.175
No, not that.

00:08:09.343 --> 00:08:11.429
In the case that things go awry,

00:08:11.929 --> 00:08:14.932
we should make preparations
to move it offshore.

00:08:15.016 --> 00:08:15.891
I spoke to

00:08:15.975 --> 00:08:18.477
the head of the Board of Audit
and Inspection yesterday.

00:08:19.061 --> 00:08:20.813
They're launching a special audit

00:08:21.564 --> 00:08:25.818
into the foreign exchange crisis
before the new administration takes over.

00:08:25.901 --> 00:08:29.947
They're clearly looking to assign blame.

00:08:30.781 --> 00:08:33.993
That could put us in the crossfire,

00:08:34.827 --> 00:08:36.287
so let's make sure

00:08:36.370 --> 00:08:39.665
our domestic funds are in order
by the end of January.

00:08:42.084 --> 00:08:43.377
Yes, sir.

00:08:43.961 --> 00:08:44.795
Good.

00:09:10.196 --> 00:09:11.322
PERSONAL INFORMATION FORM

00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:24.085
PERSONAL INFORMATION FORM
HONG KEUM-BO

00:09:24.168 --> 00:09:26.045
EMPLOYEE PERSONNEL RECORD

00:09:26.128 --> 00:09:27.213
{\an8}HONG CHUN-SEOP, FATHER
KIM SOON-JUNG, MOTHER

00:09:29.090 --> 00:09:30.591
{\an8}HONG JANG-MI, YOUNGER SISTER

00:09:36.555 --> 00:09:38.891
If the chairman finds out
the OW's slush fund is gone,

00:09:40.601 --> 00:09:42.812
thirty years of work
will go down the drain.

00:09:52.655 --> 00:09:53.489
Hey.

00:09:53.572 --> 00:09:54.573
Ju-ran.

00:09:55.366 --> 00:09:57.451
Yeah, I looked into it.

00:10:00.079 --> 00:10:03.207
I went to the restaurant
that Hong Keum-bo's parents run,

00:10:03.290 --> 00:10:05.418
and I even saw
the real Hong Jang-mi there.

00:10:06.711 --> 00:10:10.131
It turns out Hong Keum-bo has been
impersonating her this whole time.

00:10:12.425 --> 00:10:13.384
So?

00:10:13.467 --> 00:10:17.096
Should I deal with her like I did
Kim I-gyeong from the Songwi Branch?

00:10:18.806 --> 00:10:19.640
No.

00:10:20.850 --> 00:10:22.101
If we act rashly,

00:10:22.935 --> 00:10:25.062
we may lose both the money
and the chairman's trust.

00:10:25.146 --> 00:10:27.231
And she couldn't have done this alone.

00:10:28.107 --> 00:10:29.275
The branch manager told us

00:10:30.067 --> 00:10:31.694
that she had an accomplice

00:10:31.777 --> 00:10:33.738
who answered the phone
and impersonated me.

00:10:38.492 --> 00:10:39.910
{\an8}SEOUL CITY DORMITORY
FOR SINGLE FEMALE WORKERS

00:10:41.620 --> 00:10:43.831
I hear you're roommates.

00:10:45.791 --> 00:10:46.917
Yes, that's right.

00:10:47.543 --> 00:10:49.336
I'll be in touch, so stand by.

00:11:02.850 --> 00:11:04.018
Ms. Go.

00:11:04.101 --> 00:11:06.145
You live in the same dorm
as Hong Jang-mi, right?

00:11:07.104 --> 00:11:08.397
Yes, that's right.

00:11:08.481 --> 00:11:09.690
Do you remember…

00:11:11.066 --> 00:11:13.986
when Madam Choi visited
the director's office and made a scene?

00:11:15.780 --> 00:11:17.531
That happens quite frequently, so…

00:11:20.451 --> 00:11:21.660
Yes, I remember.

00:11:24.121 --> 00:11:25.122
Can you tell me…

00:11:26.832 --> 00:11:29.043
your whereabouts at that time?

00:11:29.919 --> 00:11:31.295
The other assistants told me

00:11:31.837 --> 00:11:35.090
that you weren't at the Admin office.

00:11:38.802 --> 00:11:40.137
I was in the president's office.

00:11:40.804 --> 00:11:44.642
President Shin was asking me
about Director Kang,

00:11:45.226 --> 00:11:49.188
since as you're well aware,
I also shared the dorms with her.

00:11:53.275 --> 00:11:55.444
When I scouted you for Hanmin,

00:11:56.403 --> 00:11:58.030
there was a minor commotion.

00:11:59.323 --> 00:12:00.950
Eulbuk Bank,

00:12:01.909 --> 00:12:03.369
Yeosan Farmers' Bank,

00:12:03.869 --> 00:12:05.120
and Saenara Bank in Yeosu.

00:12:06.413 --> 00:12:07.665
The branch managers there

00:12:08.541 --> 00:12:11.794
wanted to bring embezzlement
and theft charges against you.

00:12:14.588 --> 00:12:15.464
I'm the one

00:12:16.465 --> 00:12:17.800
who covered that up.

00:12:20.219 --> 00:12:22.096
One call from me is all it takes

00:12:22.179 --> 00:12:23.764
to rile them up again.

00:12:25.975 --> 00:12:26.850
So,

00:12:27.935 --> 00:12:30.980
you should be very careful
about the side you take.

00:12:32.565 --> 00:12:34.149
"Don't bite the hand that feeds you."

00:12:35.150 --> 00:12:36.277
"If you do,

00:12:36.360 --> 00:12:37.444
it'll be your undoing."

00:12:38.112 --> 00:12:39.697
They say that for a reason.

00:12:43.951 --> 00:12:45.703
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

00:12:45.786 --> 00:12:48.289
I think Ms. Song has caught on.

00:12:48.872 --> 00:12:52.501
She summoned me today
and threatened me with my past,

00:12:52.585 --> 00:12:53.877
telling me to join her side.

00:12:53.961 --> 00:12:55.087
You told Ms. Hong, right?

00:12:55.170 --> 00:12:56.880
I told her right away.

00:12:56.964 --> 00:12:59.758
I told her to be extra careful,
but you know she never listens.

00:13:00.884 --> 00:13:04.305
What do you normally do
when you find yourself cornered like this?

00:13:05.639 --> 00:13:07.600
I run and don't look back.

00:13:20.529 --> 00:13:22.197
Just relax. You're still recovering.

00:13:22.281 --> 00:13:24.116
I'm being discharged tomorrow.

00:13:29.204 --> 00:13:31.457
The RA caught us with Bom,

00:13:31.540 --> 00:13:34.043
so I had my parents in Incheon
look after her.

00:13:34.585 --> 00:13:38.631
My parents suggested
that you and Bom stay with them.

00:13:43.636 --> 00:13:44.845
Thank you.

00:13:47.181 --> 00:13:49.600
You're thanking Hong Keum-bo
and not Hong Jang-mi, right?

00:13:51.268 --> 00:13:53.896
I thought I had everyone fooled,

00:13:54.438 --> 00:13:55.898
but I had failed from the start.

00:13:57.816 --> 00:14:00.903
Thank you for keeping my secret.

00:14:01.904 --> 00:14:02.946
It was nothing.

00:14:03.530 --> 00:14:07.242
I'm the one who left you
with all sorts of requests,

00:14:08.202 --> 00:14:10.663
only to survive a suicide attempt
and burden you even more

00:14:10.746 --> 00:14:12.206
with my daughter and me.

00:14:14.083 --> 00:14:16.210
But you know…

00:14:19.254 --> 00:14:20.673
I really wanted to live.

00:14:38.148 --> 00:14:39.900
My parents run a fried chicken restaurant.

00:14:40.609 --> 00:14:43.153
If you feel that bad,
help them out when they're busy.

00:14:44.488 --> 00:14:48.200
Although they're rarely busy
because of the recession and all.

00:14:56.083 --> 00:14:57.626
Where's Room 315?

00:14:58.252 --> 00:14:59.878
It's that way.

00:15:10.597 --> 00:15:11.473
Ms. Hong.

00:15:12.558 --> 00:15:13.684
No, that's not right.

00:15:13.767 --> 00:15:16.937
Perhaps I should be more respectful
and address you as "Inspector Hong"?

00:15:17.021 --> 00:15:19.857
Showing up unannounced
is already pretty disrespectful.

00:15:21.191 --> 00:15:22.443
Are you here for an overdue visit?

00:15:25.571 --> 00:15:28.198
I have no business with some forgettable,
nameless bank teller.

00:15:30.325 --> 00:15:31.618
You should remember her.

00:15:32.411 --> 00:15:33.454
You all are responsible.

00:15:43.297 --> 00:15:44.882
Do you even know whose money you touched?

00:15:47.134 --> 00:15:48.510
Of course, I do.

00:15:48.594 --> 00:15:51.847
It's Hong Jang-mi's money
that fell out of the sky and into her lap.

00:15:56.810 --> 00:15:59.063
Ms. Song,
you initiated the physical force.

00:16:00.397 --> 00:16:03.942
What happened to the champion of justice
leading the crusade against Hanmin?

00:16:04.026 --> 00:16:07.029
I see even the esteemed Hong Keum-bo
is tempted by money.

00:16:07.654 --> 00:16:09.948
Did you fake your identity to get the job

00:16:10.032 --> 00:16:12.618
so you could trade in your experience
for 24 billion won?

00:16:12.701 --> 00:16:14.328
You were after the money all along!

00:16:15.537 --> 00:16:16.663
You should know

00:16:16.747 --> 00:16:18.123
you won't be alive to spend it.

00:16:18.874 --> 00:16:20.250
How sad your parents will be

00:16:20.334 --> 00:16:23.295
when their beloved daughter
meets her untimely death.

00:16:23.378 --> 00:16:26.465
Your own future should concern you
more than mine does.

00:16:26.965 --> 00:16:28.842
Do you think
Chairman Kang will let you live

00:16:28.926 --> 00:16:30.803
once he finds out his 24 billion is gone?

00:16:40.145 --> 00:16:43.357
The accomplice who impersonated me
to help you withdraw from Saenara Bank was

00:16:43.440 --> 00:16:44.274
Go Bok-hee, right?

00:16:45.859 --> 00:16:47.236
Are you even aware

00:16:47.319 --> 00:16:51.240
of how many banks and securities firms
she has ripped off so far?

00:16:51.323 --> 00:16:53.033
Do you really think
the money you two stole

00:16:53.117 --> 00:16:54.409
will be safe in her hands?

00:16:54.493 --> 00:16:57.913
If you want your 24 billion back,
you will do as I say.

00:16:59.373 --> 00:17:01.959
I'll hand over the money
if you get rid of President Shin.

00:17:03.460 --> 00:17:04.962
President Shin?

00:17:05.045 --> 00:17:07.005
He's your real enemy,

00:17:07.089 --> 00:17:09.716
the one looking to strip Hanmin bare
and swallow it whole.

00:17:10.259 --> 00:17:12.136
If Hanmin goes down,

00:17:12.219 --> 00:17:14.429
both your hard work and mine
will go up in smoke.

00:17:19.017 --> 00:17:20.310
Be sure to answer my calls.

00:17:46.962 --> 00:17:48.338
So what did Ms. Song say?

00:17:48.422 --> 00:17:49.423
Did she say she'd do it?

00:17:49.506 --> 00:17:50.799
That she'd get rid of President Shin?

00:17:50.883 --> 00:17:52.593
I didn't bother waiting for a response.

00:17:52.676 --> 00:17:54.386
She has no other choice but to follow.

00:17:55.637 --> 00:17:58.390
After being loyal to Chairman Kang
all this time,

00:17:58.473 --> 00:18:00.601
how'd she end up in Hong Keum-bo's snare?

00:18:01.143 --> 00:18:02.019
Oh, right.

00:18:03.520 --> 00:18:05.814
She mentioned your name
almost immediately.

00:18:06.315 --> 00:18:08.400
She also knew
about your past embezzlement.

00:18:11.028 --> 00:18:13.155
Looks like work tomorrow
is going to be torture.

00:18:15.532 --> 00:18:17.701
A-E-I-O-U.

00:18:19.161 --> 00:18:20.662
Did you call for me, ma'am?

00:18:23.040 --> 00:18:25.542
You know, I've been wondering for a while.

00:18:25.626 --> 00:18:28.879
How do you manage to maintain
such a calm smile on your face

00:18:28.962 --> 00:18:31.548
when the higher-ups
spew nonsense and dig into you?

00:18:35.761 --> 00:18:36.637
It's so I don't lose.

00:18:37.846 --> 00:18:40.849
You lose if you show tears
or falter in that moment.

00:18:42.351 --> 00:18:45.145
I know how I really feel
behind that smile.

00:18:49.524 --> 00:18:50.859
Now I know too.

00:18:54.112 --> 00:18:56.615
I'm afraid I don't understand, ma'am.

00:18:57.783 --> 00:18:58.742
Watch and learn.

00:19:03.455 --> 00:19:05.040
Yes, I understand.

00:19:09.544 --> 00:19:12.130
I just faxed over
Go Bok-hee's personnel file.

00:19:12.214 --> 00:19:13.423
EMPLOYEE PERSONNEL RECORD

00:19:13.507 --> 00:19:15.592
Her older brother's name is Go Bok-cheol.

00:19:16.176 --> 00:19:19.263
He's a convicted violent offender
who was just released a month ago.

00:19:19.888 --> 00:19:20.722
Find him.

00:19:32.567 --> 00:19:34.403
Hey, what's with the long face?

00:19:35.779 --> 00:19:39.616
I know it's the recession and all,
but you need to keep your spirits up.

00:19:42.786 --> 00:19:44.246
How are the preparations
for the engagement going?

00:19:46.790 --> 00:19:48.333
I couldn't be busier.

00:19:48.417 --> 00:19:50.460
I have another packed day ahead.

00:19:50.544 --> 00:19:52.671
I have a catering testing at lunch,

00:19:52.754 --> 00:19:53.755
and in the afternoon,

00:19:53.839 --> 00:19:56.008
I'm checking Nora and President Shin's
astrological compatibility.

00:19:57.843 --> 00:19:58.885
Ma'am.

00:20:00.262 --> 00:20:01.221
Have you looked into

00:20:01.305 --> 00:20:03.140
President Shin's
past relationships as well?

00:20:05.642 --> 00:20:07.019
Why the sudden interest?

00:20:07.102 --> 00:20:09.896
As you're well aware,

00:20:09.980 --> 00:20:11.898
he's lived abroad for a long time,

00:20:11.982 --> 00:20:14.234
so the available intel was a bit limited.

00:20:14.318 --> 00:20:16.611
He dated his first love in college,

00:20:16.695 --> 00:20:18.822
and they got their first jobs
at the same company.

00:20:18.905 --> 00:20:19.740
That's about it.

00:20:20.949 --> 00:20:21.783
But you know what?

00:20:22.409 --> 00:20:24.077
She has such a funny name.

00:20:24.161 --> 00:20:26.204
"Hong Keum-bo." Isn't it funny?

00:20:27.289 --> 00:20:28.665
Did you say Hong Keum-bo?

00:20:28.749 --> 00:20:31.960
You know, like the Hong Kong action star
Hung Kam-bo.

00:20:35.964 --> 00:20:37.632
Don't tell Nora.

00:20:39.676 --> 00:20:41.178
I should go and escort the chairman.

00:20:42.804 --> 00:20:43.722
"Hong Keum-bo."

00:20:50.395 --> 00:20:53.357
So she's targeting Shin Jung-woo
for a reason.

00:20:57.235 --> 00:20:59.821
There's a party buying up Hanmin stocks?

00:20:59.905 --> 00:21:02.074
They acquired over 9% last week alone.

00:21:02.157 --> 00:21:04.451
- Is it an investment trust company?
- An investment trust company?

00:21:04.534 --> 00:21:07.037
I'm not sure,
but it's definitely not an individual.

00:21:07.621 --> 00:21:08.955
There haven't been public disclosures yet.

00:21:09.623 --> 00:21:11.166
All right, I'll look into it.

00:21:20.258 --> 00:21:21.885
Ms. Go, can I see you for a moment?

00:21:30.852 --> 00:21:33.563
{\an8}Do you happen to know
of a long-tenured employee

00:21:33.647 --> 00:21:37.109
who has their finger
on the pulse of the securities industry?

00:21:37.192 --> 00:21:38.985
May I ask what this is regarding?

00:21:39.069 --> 00:21:41.780
We lost many people
during the restructuring.

00:21:41.863 --> 00:21:45.534
I would say Mr. Cha Jung-il from Research
has a strong grasp of market sentiment.

00:21:46.451 --> 00:21:47.953
Let him know I'd like a meeting.

00:21:48.036 --> 00:21:49.079
Yes, sir.

00:22:01.216 --> 00:22:02.759
You asked to see me, sir?

00:22:03.343 --> 00:22:04.219
Yes.

00:22:04.302 --> 00:22:07.472
I'd like to ask you for a favor

00:22:07.556 --> 00:22:08.515
off the record.

00:22:08.598 --> 00:22:10.976
Yes, whatever you need.
Just say the word, sir.

00:22:12.227 --> 00:22:16.773
I'd like to find out if there have been
any shareholding changes

00:22:16.857 --> 00:22:20.026
among Hanmin executives
or anyone in the chairman's inner circle.

00:22:21.695 --> 00:22:23.238
Gosh, sir. Are you already…

00:22:23.822 --> 00:22:25.407
that well-informed?

00:22:27.117 --> 00:22:28.869
Who else knows about this?

00:22:28.952 --> 00:22:30.328
Ms. Song Ju-ran…

00:22:33.540 --> 00:22:37.711
Walk me through
exactly what you reported to her.

00:22:38.753 --> 00:22:41.423
Darn it, this big mouth of mine…

00:22:46.678 --> 00:22:47.888
Hold on.

00:22:51.600 --> 00:22:55.604
Executive Director Oh Deok-gyu
disposed of his entire holding

00:22:55.687 --> 00:22:57.355
except for one share.

00:22:57.939 --> 00:22:59.858
It comes to nearly 9%.

00:23:00.942 --> 00:23:01.776
And this is something…

00:23:03.320 --> 00:23:05.739
that I didn't even disclose to Ms. Song.

00:23:06.656 --> 00:23:10.702
I finally uncovered the buyer's name.

00:23:11.244 --> 00:23:12.329
Who is it?

00:23:15.707 --> 00:23:17.542
It's a name you would've heard of as well.

00:23:18.919 --> 00:23:20.337
Right, so who is it?

00:23:23.798 --> 00:23:25.217
Yeouido Pirates.

00:23:26.218 --> 00:23:27.844
I even found out the name of its CEO.

00:23:29.512 --> 00:23:31.389
"Hong Keum-bo."

00:23:36.353 --> 00:23:37.771
Before you joined us, Mr. Shin,

00:23:37.854 --> 00:23:40.815
the prosecutors probed into
Hanmin's slush fund,

00:23:40.899 --> 00:23:43.985
and one of the FSS members involved then
was named Hong Keum-bo.

00:23:44.069 --> 00:23:45.737
It could be just a namesake,

00:23:45.820 --> 00:23:47.614
but it's not a common name, you know?

00:23:47.697 --> 00:23:49.449
Hong Keum-bo is rather rare, isn't it?

00:23:49.532 --> 00:23:51.785
Thank you. That will do.

00:23:51.868 --> 00:23:52.702
You may leave.

00:23:53.286 --> 00:23:54.371
Oh, already?

00:24:05.590 --> 00:24:06.675
Sir.

00:24:07.217 --> 00:24:10.303
The short-term bonds mature
next Wednesday.

00:24:11.763 --> 00:24:15.892
President Shin, DK Ventures will be able
to assist us again this time, right?

00:24:16.601 --> 00:24:19.104
Yes, I'll let them know in advance.

00:24:19.187 --> 00:24:20.855
No, there's no need.

00:24:20.939 --> 00:24:23.692
That will be unnecessary this time.

00:24:23.775 --> 00:24:25.568
I'm planning to tap into the reserves

00:24:25.652 --> 00:24:28.738
set aside for employee wages
and severance pay.

00:24:28.822 --> 00:24:30.490
You can't do that, sir.

00:24:30.573 --> 00:24:34.119
The restructuring has already strained
internal sentiment and working conditions,

00:24:34.703 --> 00:24:36.371
so that may accelerate staff turnover.

00:24:36.454 --> 00:24:38.415
That's exactly what I'm after.

00:24:38.957 --> 00:24:40.542
When the company is struggling,

00:24:40.625 --> 00:24:43.545
the employees should share
some of the burden.

00:24:44.546 --> 00:24:45.714
Also,

00:24:45.797 --> 00:24:48.174
I heard this at one of my gatherings.

00:24:49.676 --> 00:24:51.594
There are rumors going around

00:24:52.178 --> 00:24:54.222
that the CEO of DK Ventures…

00:24:55.890 --> 00:24:59.269
has been staying in Korea
and shopping around for companies.

00:25:01.896 --> 00:25:04.566
Given the undervaluation
of the Korean stock market,

00:25:04.649 --> 00:25:06.276
I believe he's considering investments.

00:25:08.737 --> 00:25:09.571
Is that so?

00:25:28.673 --> 00:25:29.632
What is it?

00:25:29.716 --> 00:25:32.135
You were the moderator of Yeouido Pirates?

00:25:32.844 --> 00:25:33.678
No.

00:25:33.762 --> 00:25:35.513
Yeouido Pirates is buying up
Hanmin stocks,

00:25:35.597 --> 00:25:37.182
and Hong Keum-bo is listed as its CEO.

00:25:37.974 --> 00:25:39.517
Yeah, that part is true.

00:25:41.978 --> 00:25:44.105
Why did you buy up Oh Deok-gyu's shares?

00:25:44.189 --> 00:25:45.023
Was a deal struck?

00:25:46.733 --> 00:25:49.986
As if he'd ever be willing
to make a deal with me.

00:25:50.070 --> 00:25:51.654
So you just swooped in then.

00:25:51.738 --> 00:25:52.697
What are you up to?

00:25:54.240 --> 00:25:58.411
I'm stopping Shin Jung-woo and DK Ventures
from destroying Hanmin.

00:25:58.495 --> 00:25:59.662
That's what I'm up to.

00:26:00.246 --> 00:26:01.331
Let's get one thing straight.

00:26:01.414 --> 00:26:03.500
It was already in ruins
before I ever got here.

00:26:03.583 --> 00:26:06.169
Just look at how Chairman Kang
manages his own company.

00:26:07.921 --> 00:26:08.755
Forget it.

00:26:09.672 --> 00:26:14.052
You're not trying to acquire shares
to seize Hanmin, right?

00:26:15.428 --> 00:26:17.889
Am I not allowed to have
the same aspirations?

00:26:19.516 --> 00:26:23.019
You're also putting on this act
while praying for Hanmin to fall.

00:26:28.233 --> 00:26:29.401
Should we make a bet?

00:26:30.318 --> 00:26:32.278
Between Hong Keum-bo and Shin Jung-woo,

00:26:32.362 --> 00:26:34.364
who do you think
will be kicked out of Hanmin first?

00:26:36.324 --> 00:26:37.867
I'll bet on you.

00:26:51.798 --> 00:26:53.425
I hope there are no misunderstandings.

00:26:53.508 --> 00:26:55.552
There won't be.

00:26:55.635 --> 00:26:57.303
I just heard everything.

00:26:58.012 --> 00:26:59.681
You summoned me, so you explain.

00:27:22.203 --> 00:27:24.747
When I saw the news about
President Kang's accident in July,

00:27:24.831 --> 00:27:26.875
I was the one
who reached out to the chairman

00:27:26.958 --> 00:27:28.877
and expressed interest in joining Hanmin.

00:27:28.960 --> 00:27:31.171
But earlier, Ms. Hong said

00:27:31.254 --> 00:27:35.425
that you and DK Ventures
were looking to destroy Hanmin.

00:27:36.134 --> 00:27:37.844
That's what I heard.

00:27:38.344 --> 00:27:40.096
That's a difference of opinion.

00:27:41.181 --> 00:27:43.975
I assume you refer to her as "Ms. Hong"

00:27:44.058 --> 00:27:47.228
because you found out
she's Hong Keum-bo and not Hong Jang-mi?

00:27:48.021 --> 00:27:50.023
Yes, but I can't tell you any more.

00:27:50.106 --> 00:27:51.608
I'm pretty loyal, you see.

00:27:52.942 --> 00:27:55.862
If people find out the lead investigator
on the slush fund probe

00:27:55.945 --> 00:27:57.947
infiltrated the company undercover,

00:27:58.698 --> 00:28:00.325
she could be in danger.

00:28:02.202 --> 00:28:04.204
It's all Kang Pil-beom's money anyway.

00:28:04.287 --> 00:28:06.456
Do you know how he made all that money?

00:28:06.539 --> 00:28:09.167
That's why she got so angry that time.

00:28:10.210 --> 00:28:12.462
Money, slush fund…

00:28:12.545 --> 00:28:14.881
That's why I pulled her aside
and tried to persuade her today.

00:28:16.549 --> 00:28:18.843
I'll make sure Keum-bo returns safely.

00:28:20.845 --> 00:28:23.139
Because you still have feelings for her?

00:28:27.393 --> 00:28:29.646
The last person my brother called…

00:28:31.606 --> 00:28:32.482
was me.

00:28:34.275 --> 00:28:35.276
When he did,

00:28:36.027 --> 00:28:38.571
I hounded him, scolded him,

00:28:40.156 --> 00:28:41.908
and told him he was naive.

00:28:42.867 --> 00:28:44.702
I yelled and cursed him out.

00:28:45.995 --> 00:28:49.082
A part of me was worried about him,
but the truth is,

00:28:49.165 --> 00:28:50.625
I was worried it could hurt me.

00:28:51.793 --> 00:28:53.419
I was more worried about myself.

00:28:54.963 --> 00:28:56.798
It became a lasting regret.

00:28:57.757 --> 00:28:59.133
You must have

00:28:59.759 --> 00:29:01.511
similar regret.

00:29:02.136 --> 00:29:04.264
What does clinging to that
so-called conscience get you?

00:29:04.347 --> 00:29:06.474
It's not about gains.
It's about not losing it!

00:29:08.017 --> 00:29:10.645
And is whatever you gain worth losing me?

00:29:13.189 --> 00:29:14.065
No.

00:29:16.150 --> 00:29:17.777
I just don't want another regret.

00:29:37.505 --> 00:29:41.050
I only followed you there yesterday
to ask about our dinner plans.

00:29:41.134 --> 00:29:42.552
I wasn't tailing you or anything.

00:29:43.803 --> 00:29:44.804
I understand.

00:29:46.055 --> 00:29:49.559
But the fact that you and Bok-hee
are hiding stuff from me

00:29:49.642 --> 00:29:50.935
makes me a bit sad.

00:29:54.856 --> 00:29:57.317
It's because we can't keep
asking you for help,

00:29:57.400 --> 00:29:59.277
and we don't want to
take advantage of you.

00:29:59.819 --> 00:30:00.653
After all,

00:30:01.946 --> 00:30:03.489
you're a part of Chairman Kang's family.

00:30:06.576 --> 00:30:08.077
The slush fund probe?

00:30:09.579 --> 00:30:11.164
Who told you about that?

00:30:11.247 --> 00:30:13.166
President Shin told me yesterday.

00:30:16.336 --> 00:30:18.129
That man is so damn useless.

00:30:20.882 --> 00:30:23.676
I'll keep it a secret.

00:30:23.760 --> 00:30:26.679
I won't do anything
that would put everyone in danger.

00:30:26.763 --> 00:30:27.597
Don't worry.

00:30:48.534 --> 00:30:49.577
Truth be told,

00:30:50.495 --> 00:30:53.581
I have no reason to show you this
before anyone else.

00:30:54.165 --> 00:30:56.459
But we're going to be family soon,

00:30:56.542 --> 00:30:59.087
and we'll both be sons-in-law. Here.

00:31:00.088 --> 00:31:01.923
Last time, with K…

00:31:02.006 --> 00:31:03.341
I mean, take a look.

00:31:04.092 --> 00:31:05.510
This will be my safety net.

00:31:06.010 --> 00:31:08.596
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES
SECOND-ROUND RESTRUCTURING LIST

00:31:14.811 --> 00:31:16.354
Can I add someone to this list?

00:31:16.437 --> 00:31:17.939
What? Who?

00:31:18.022 --> 00:31:21.234
There was that female employee who was
almost fired after the order-entry error.

00:31:22.694 --> 00:31:25.905
We had to tread lightly and be mindful
of public opinion back then, but now…

00:31:25.989 --> 00:31:28.199
Right, this would be the ideal time.

00:31:28.282 --> 00:31:29.951
In fact, there was an article

00:31:30.034 --> 00:31:33.788
about "voluntary restructuring"
in the politics section of today's paper.

00:31:33.871 --> 00:31:36.916
That's actually
the administration sending a signal.

00:31:37.000 --> 00:31:39.877
We should take this chance
to clear out the troublemakers

00:31:39.961 --> 00:31:41.713
and the deadweight.

00:31:42.380 --> 00:31:44.215
Regarding funds…

00:31:44.298 --> 00:31:46.259
Never mind. Write down the name.

00:31:49.053 --> 00:31:54.225
HONG JANG-MI

00:32:05.319 --> 00:32:07.697
It's customary for female staff decisions
to go through me.

00:32:08.948 --> 00:32:11.492
Please postpone
the second round of restructuring.

00:32:12.368 --> 00:32:14.662
We should revisit it
after I conduct a thorough review--

00:32:14.746 --> 00:32:17.165
And what if I disagree with that custom?

00:32:18.291 --> 00:32:20.793
A chief of staff
controlling HR at a company

00:32:20.877 --> 00:32:22.920
and only for one gender at that?

00:32:23.588 --> 00:32:24.714
Since when has this been the norm?

00:32:26.632 --> 00:32:28.885
That's not a custom
but an abuse of authority.

00:32:30.136 --> 00:32:31.804
Follow your superior's directive.

00:32:32.430 --> 00:32:33.639
You may leave.

00:32:51.324 --> 00:32:53.159
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES
SECOND-ROUND RESTRUCTURING LIST

00:32:56.120 --> 00:32:57.872
RESEARCH DIVISION: HONG JANG-MI

00:32:59.207 --> 00:33:00.541
Well done, Mr. Oh.

00:33:01.292 --> 00:33:02.919
Have you reviewed it, Mr. Shin?

00:33:03.002 --> 00:33:04.337
Yes, sir. I have no objections.

00:33:04.420 --> 00:33:05.254
Good.

00:33:06.005 --> 00:33:06.881
Let's see here.

00:33:06.964 --> 00:33:08.132
Sir.

00:33:09.550 --> 00:33:11.552
I haven't had the chance to review it.

00:33:12.345 --> 00:33:14.764
Could you perhaps delay
the final decision a bit, sir?

00:33:16.099 --> 00:33:18.935
I had Executive Director Oh
take care of it for a reason.

00:33:19.018 --> 00:33:23.231
You already have your hands full
with Nora's wedding preparations.

00:33:24.232 --> 00:33:27.110
With the Lunar New Year holiday coming up,
it'd be better to proceed now.

00:33:27.193 --> 00:33:30.363
Given her involvement
in the order-entry incident,

00:33:30.863 --> 00:33:32.990
Ms. Hong Jang-mi
poses a risk of internal discord.

00:33:33.074 --> 00:33:36.119
But she was
the Outstanding Woman last quarter.

00:33:37.036 --> 00:33:39.747
Imagine what everyone would say
about our performance review system

00:33:39.831 --> 00:33:41.999
if we terminated an employee
who was just honored.

00:33:42.083 --> 00:33:43.209
That's enough.

00:33:43.292 --> 00:33:47.672
Is it worth all this fuss
over just one female employee?

00:33:47.755 --> 00:33:50.466
Perhaps we can just
keep her on the payroll

00:33:51.050 --> 00:33:53.427
and tuck her away somewhere out of sight?

00:34:00.059 --> 00:34:01.936
How can they just spring this on us?

00:34:02.645 --> 00:34:05.189
They never post stuff like this
on the intranet.

00:34:10.570 --> 00:34:11.529
Ms. Hong.

00:34:11.612 --> 00:34:13.281
I'm not the least bit surprised.

00:34:13.781 --> 00:34:16.075
It's time you faced
society's bitter realities.

00:34:16.909 --> 00:34:18.995
You should be grateful
they didn't just fire you.

00:34:19.871 --> 00:34:22.957
Mr. Cha, you should also read
the announcement below.

00:34:25.042 --> 00:34:27.753
{\an8}DEPUTY MANAGERS AND ABOVE WILL RECEIVE
THEIR JANUARY SALARY IN FEBRUARY

00:34:27.837 --> 00:34:29.630
We're not getting paid this month?

00:34:29.714 --> 00:34:32.675
The bitter realities of society
don't discriminate by status.

00:34:33.176 --> 00:34:35.052
You're not exempt either.

00:34:49.442 --> 00:34:50.943
DEPUTY MANAGERS AND ABOVE WILL RECEIVE
THEIR JANUARY SALARY IN FEBRUARY

00:34:59.410 --> 00:35:01.412
Deputy managers and above
are going to be paid late.

00:35:02.413 --> 00:35:04.916
Man, I should've left with you back then.

00:35:06.000 --> 00:35:09.045
Don't say things you don't mean.
Just hang in there, no matter what.

00:35:09.712 --> 00:35:10.963
Let's drink tonight.

00:35:11.547 --> 00:35:13.424
I can't, I'm…

00:35:15.635 --> 00:35:16.719
I have plans.

00:35:16.802 --> 00:35:18.012
Let's talk later.

00:35:18.095 --> 00:35:18.971
I'll call you.

00:35:19.764 --> 00:35:21.807
All right. Just hang up already.

00:35:22.808 --> 00:35:23.643
Bang…

00:35:46.874 --> 00:35:49.835
1998 EXPERIENCED CANDIDATES INTERVIEW

00:35:54.966 --> 00:35:56.092
Mr. Bang Jin-mok?

00:35:56.175 --> 00:35:57.593
Yes. Here.

00:36:02.390 --> 00:36:03.599
SINYONG BANK
HONG KEUM-BO, ACCOUNT HISTORY

00:36:03.683 --> 00:36:04.684
JOGEOK BANK
HONG KEUM-BO, ACCOUNT HISTORY

00:36:08.229 --> 00:36:09.563
ACCOUNT HOLDER: HONG JANG-MI

00:36:11.440 --> 00:36:14.277
ACCOUNT HISTORY
ACCOUNT HOLDER: GO BOK-HEE

00:36:16.988 --> 00:36:18.906
Hong Keum-bo, Hong Jang-mi,
and even Go Bok-hee.

00:36:19.657 --> 00:36:20.950
None of them have
such transaction records.

00:36:21.033 --> 00:36:25.204
Could they have used
a borrowed-name account?

00:36:25.871 --> 00:36:26.789
No.

00:36:27.999 --> 00:36:29.625
I tracked the checks,

00:36:29.709 --> 00:36:31.585
and they were cashed out by someone else.

00:36:32.586 --> 00:36:33.796
They've already exchanged them.

00:36:34.630 --> 00:36:36.299
They have the money in cash.

00:36:37.591 --> 00:36:39.969
I can't beat her down,
and I can't kick her to the curb.

00:36:40.052 --> 00:36:43.931
I had Go Bok-cheol tail Hong Keum-bo.

00:36:44.432 --> 00:36:48.936
But she only ever goes to her apartment,
the office, and the dorms.

00:36:51.063 --> 00:36:52.023
It's in the dorm.

00:36:54.483 --> 00:36:56.277
Start by searching Room 301.

00:37:02.575 --> 00:37:03.451
SEOUL CITY DORMITORY
FOR SINGLE FEMALE WORKERS

00:37:03.534 --> 00:37:06.162
It might've started out
as Hong Keum-bo's personal objective,

00:37:06.245 --> 00:37:07.246
but not anymore.

00:37:07.330 --> 00:37:09.749
You're in the driver's seat, so drive.

00:37:09.832 --> 00:37:12.084
Why aren't you doing anything
with the money?

00:37:12.752 --> 00:37:15.963
I want to take care of Shin Jung-woo first
before I make my move.

00:37:16.630 --> 00:37:20.176
One by one, we need to take out anyone
Chairman Kang trusts enough

00:37:20.843 --> 00:37:23.346
to use against us
when he finds out about our plan.

00:37:23.846 --> 00:37:25.765
Shin Jung-woo is the first target.

00:37:26.807 --> 00:37:28.351
ELIMINATING CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM'S
INNER CIRCLE

00:37:28.434 --> 00:37:30.394
{\an8}ALBERT OH: ON OUR SIDE
KANG NORA: ?

00:37:30.478 --> 00:37:31.729
{\an8}STEP 1: PRESIDENT SHIN JUNG-WOO

00:37:32.688 --> 00:37:36.067
I'm surprised you're not suggesting
that we flee with the money.

00:37:37.401 --> 00:37:38.569
Don't be so sure I won't.

00:39:08.033 --> 00:39:09.994
- Jang-mi.
- I'm fine, so get out of here.

00:39:10.077 --> 00:39:11.036
Now!

00:39:13.372 --> 00:39:14.373
But Bom,

00:39:14.957 --> 00:39:17.084
I'll hold onto this
because it's dangerous.

00:39:22.923 --> 00:39:23.924
No, wait. Stop.

00:39:24.008 --> 00:39:25.342
Get out of here quietly,

00:39:25.426 --> 00:39:26.969
or I'll burn all this money!

00:39:30.598 --> 00:39:31.932
Help!

00:39:42.776 --> 00:39:43.944
- What's going on?
- What's happening?

00:39:44.028 --> 00:39:45.279
Is there a fire in Room 301?

00:39:45.362 --> 00:39:46.363
It's a burglar!

00:39:46.447 --> 00:39:47.615
We've got a burglar!

00:39:52.703 --> 00:39:53.787
Damn it.

00:40:11.430 --> 00:40:12.306
Damn it.

00:40:12.848 --> 00:40:14.266
How dare you break in here?

00:40:14.350 --> 00:40:15.809
- What's this now?
- Stop right there!

00:40:16.519 --> 00:40:17.728
Stop!

00:40:21.023 --> 00:40:23.025
- You punk!
- Stop right there!

00:40:32.660 --> 00:40:33.494
You bastard!

00:40:35.371 --> 00:40:36.205
Where did he go?

00:40:37.206 --> 00:40:38.290
Where did that punk go?

00:40:39.250 --> 00:40:40.167
- That bastard.
- What was that?

00:40:49.510 --> 00:40:51.470
Jang-mi, open this door!

00:40:54.390 --> 00:40:56.016
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

00:40:56.100 --> 00:40:58.143
Did you set off the fire alarm?

00:40:58.227 --> 00:40:59.478
Tell me you're okay first!

00:40:59.562 --> 00:41:00.813
I'm fine.

00:41:00.896 --> 00:41:03.107
He ran off
as soon as the fire alarm went off.

00:41:09.321 --> 00:41:11.740
I thought you'd be worried
about the money,

00:41:11.824 --> 00:41:13.492
but you worried about me first.

00:41:13.576 --> 00:41:14.827
Seriously?

00:41:14.910 --> 00:41:18.372
I may be crazy about money,
but of course I'd save you first!

00:41:18.455 --> 00:41:20.916
Do you really think I'd run away
just to save myself?

00:41:24.378 --> 00:41:25.254
It's okay.

00:41:25.754 --> 00:41:27.089
I hate you!

00:41:35.889 --> 00:41:37.308
I wasn't able to catch the burglar.

00:41:37.391 --> 00:41:38.392
Are you two all right?

00:41:39.310 --> 00:41:40.185
Is there anything missing?

00:41:40.686 --> 00:41:41.895
I'll go to your room now--

00:41:41.979 --> 00:41:43.731
- It's okay.
- Nothing is missing.

00:41:45.316 --> 00:41:46.525
I reported it to the police.

00:41:47.109 --> 00:41:48.902
They said they'll reinforce patrol units,

00:41:48.986 --> 00:41:51.238
but please be sure to lock your doors.

00:41:52.031 --> 00:41:52.948
Thank you.

00:41:58.871 --> 00:42:01.790
I recognized his face.

00:42:02.583 --> 00:42:03.500
What?

00:42:03.584 --> 00:42:05.878
I was almost kidnapped once
before I moved in here,

00:42:06.670 --> 00:42:08.714
and he was the man
driving the van back then.

00:42:09.757 --> 00:42:12.384
He was also involved in
Kang Myeong-hwi's accident.

00:42:14.303 --> 00:42:15.721
Ms. Song must've sent him, right?

00:42:17.473 --> 00:42:18.515
Probably.

00:42:25.147 --> 00:42:28.359
HANMIN INVESTMENT & SECURITIES

00:42:38.911 --> 00:42:40.329
What are you doing here
at the head office?

00:42:41.455 --> 00:42:42.665
You were transferred.

00:42:42.748 --> 00:42:45.501
After the first restructuring
last December,

00:42:45.584 --> 00:42:48.962
the female employees signed a separate,
additional employment contract.

00:42:52.675 --> 00:42:54.343
See right there? A one-year contract.

00:42:54.426 --> 00:42:55.260
EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT

00:42:55.886 --> 00:42:58.013
Ordering a transfer to a remote region

00:42:58.097 --> 00:43:00.599
with no personal ties
and without a valid reason

00:43:00.683 --> 00:43:02.726
is clearly an unjust personnel action.

00:43:03.936 --> 00:43:06.438
You should be complaining about this
to President Shin, not me.

00:43:07.815 --> 00:43:10.192
That would be the end
of Hong Jang-mi's complaint.

00:43:11.402 --> 00:43:12.986
Now, we'll move on to Hong Keum-bo's.

00:43:15.197 --> 00:43:18.075
You attempted
quite an ambitious stunt last night.

00:43:18.158 --> 00:43:20.703
I assume Mr. Auto Repair Shop
reported back?

00:43:21.328 --> 00:43:23.455
You hid all that money in a dorm room?

00:43:25.499 --> 00:43:27.042
Now that you've confirmed that,

00:43:27.584 --> 00:43:29.795
you just have to make a decision.

00:43:31.338 --> 00:43:35.384
I believe our deal remains on the table.

00:43:44.643 --> 00:43:47.312
In the meantime,
we'll quietly accumulate more bonds.

00:43:48.647 --> 00:43:50.858
And if Hanmin goes bankrupt on its own?
That's a win for us.

00:43:51.442 --> 00:43:52.776
If he continues to hold out,

00:43:52.860 --> 00:43:55.904
we'll take over Hanmin
with a surprise court receivership filing

00:43:56.488 --> 00:43:58.532
{\an8}and spruce it up to sell it.

00:43:58.615 --> 00:43:59.616
Then

00:43:59.700 --> 00:44:01.744
all of Yeouido
will be in the palm of our hands.

00:44:04.079 --> 00:44:08.041
DK Ventures has already been in contact
with other Korean companies.

00:44:09.460 --> 00:44:12.713
I'm sure they'll try to avoid the fallout
of their investment plans

00:44:12.796 --> 00:44:15.340
by cutting Shin Jung-woo loose.

00:44:25.559 --> 00:44:27.436
If Hanmin ends up in their hands,

00:44:27.519 --> 00:44:29.688
the 12th floor will be the first
to get wiped out.

00:44:30.856 --> 00:44:33.859
Do you want to be kicked out
after running errands for 30 years?

00:44:38.071 --> 00:44:41.575
Are you sure your personal grudge
against him isn't clouding your judgment?

00:44:43.160 --> 00:44:44.661
I see you've done some digging.

00:44:45.579 --> 00:44:46.789
A university alum,

00:44:47.456 --> 00:44:49.750
co-workers at your first job as a CPA,

00:44:50.584 --> 00:44:52.127
and ex-lovers.

00:44:53.128 --> 00:44:55.255
You two were passionate in your twenties.

00:44:57.424 --> 00:45:01.053
You can choose whichever card works best,

00:45:01.553 --> 00:45:02.804
then play it with Chairman Kang.

00:45:03.555 --> 00:45:04.681
I couldn't care less.

00:45:29.414 --> 00:45:30.999
Why those punks…

00:45:31.792 --> 00:45:33.377
They have the audacity

00:45:33.460 --> 00:45:36.171
to eye my company with mere chump change?

00:45:36.255 --> 00:45:39.341
Ms. Kang and President Shin's
engagement party is tomorrow.

00:45:40.217 --> 00:45:42.177
We need to act quickly.

00:45:43.011 --> 00:45:44.721
You know,

00:45:44.805 --> 00:45:51.770
if DK Ventures floods the market
with all the Hanmin bonds they have,

00:45:52.312 --> 00:45:55.023
then we will be helpless.

00:45:55.107 --> 00:45:56.858
Us failing to secure the public funds

00:45:56.942 --> 00:46:00.237
was a part of Shin Jung-woo's plan
to set the stage for DK Ventures.

00:46:00.946 --> 00:46:02.072
You're right.

00:46:02.864 --> 00:46:05.367
I only let him off the hook for that

00:46:05.450 --> 00:46:07.494
because he secured the funds immediately.

00:46:08.620 --> 00:46:10.247
As you are already aware,

00:46:10.831 --> 00:46:14.960
DK Ventures is actively investing
in other Korean companies as well.

00:46:15.752 --> 00:46:17.254
I'm sure the CEO would rather

00:46:17.838 --> 00:46:20.340
cut Shin Jung-woo than take major losses.

00:46:22.259 --> 00:46:25.512
I will meet with him tomorrow

00:46:25.596 --> 00:46:27.723
and confirm it myself.

00:46:33.395 --> 00:46:36.273
A hostile takeover?
You've misunderstood, sir.

00:46:36.857 --> 00:46:38.650
Hanmin was the one who suggested

00:46:38.734 --> 00:46:40.319
the issuance of bonds over an investment.

00:46:40.402 --> 00:46:41.445
No.

00:46:41.528 --> 00:46:42.779
To be exact,

00:46:43.614 --> 00:46:45.699
that was Shin Jung-woo's suggestion.

00:46:46.992 --> 00:46:51.246
Why would the infiltrator
planted by DK Ventures

00:46:52.080 --> 00:46:54.166
ever work for me, huh?

00:46:54.249 --> 00:46:55.876
That's pure speculation.

00:46:56.460 --> 00:46:59.212
Why don't you invite President Shin
and ask him yourself?

00:46:59.296 --> 00:47:02.382
The original intent
may have been questionable,

00:47:03.216 --> 00:47:05.302
but the result is what counts.

00:47:06.136 --> 00:47:07.012
I, for one,

00:47:07.095 --> 00:47:11.600
do not wish to ruin
my relationship with DK Ventures.

00:47:14.978 --> 00:47:18.398
I'm trying to tell you
that everything will be settled

00:47:18.482 --> 00:47:19.691
if we handle one person.

00:47:21.652 --> 00:47:23.820
…and spruce it up to sell it.

00:47:23.904 --> 00:47:26.740
Then all of Yeouido
will be in the palm of our hands.

00:47:29.743 --> 00:47:33.080
Have you been recording
every conversation in my office like this?

00:47:34.665 --> 00:47:35.832
That's not what's important.

00:47:38.043 --> 00:47:41.296
Leave the company quietly.

00:47:41.380 --> 00:47:43.048
That is the chairman's wish.

00:47:43.131 --> 00:47:45.050
And why would I take orders from you?

00:47:46.343 --> 00:47:47.636
At least

00:47:48.553 --> 00:47:52.307
I didn't disclose to the chairman
what I know about Hong Keum-bo.

00:47:52.391 --> 00:47:54.184
You must be saving it for leverage later!

00:47:58.563 --> 00:48:01.024
I will speak to the chairman myself.

00:48:12.452 --> 00:48:15.831
LIST OF KOREAN COMPANIES, 1998

00:48:16.498 --> 00:48:17.374
Here.

00:48:19.292 --> 00:48:20.293
Does that look familiar?

00:48:21.253 --> 00:48:25.924
It's the list of Korean companies
DK Ventures approached

00:48:26.007 --> 00:48:28.427
using their shell company.

00:48:28.510 --> 00:48:32.931
You call yourself a venture firm,
claiming to back startups.

00:48:33.515 --> 00:48:35.767
But every company
you targeted overseas was

00:48:36.393 --> 00:48:38.812
a solid mid-sized corporation.

00:48:39.646 --> 00:48:42.232
Did you really think
I'd enter into business with someone

00:48:42.315 --> 00:48:44.484
without doing due diligence?

00:48:45.235 --> 00:48:49.072
I may not be able to make you prosper,
but I can certainly ruin you.

00:48:49.573 --> 00:48:52.701
I can make sure
your Korean investments go up in smoke

00:48:53.285 --> 00:48:55.787
and shut you out
of the Korean market for good.

00:48:55.871 --> 00:48:56.788
Sir.

00:48:56.872 --> 00:48:58.123
Thanks to you,

00:48:58.206 --> 00:49:02.169
I'll be painted as the patriotic old guard
who fought off foreign capital

00:49:03.044 --> 00:49:04.921
to save his company

00:49:05.922 --> 00:49:10.343
and shield other Korean firms
from being devoured.

00:49:14.723 --> 00:49:17.434
If we just push out Shin Jung-woo,

00:49:17.517 --> 00:49:21.062
we could all maintain peace.

00:49:23.023 --> 00:49:26.943
You only have
the company's fate on the line,

00:49:27.778 --> 00:49:28.653
but for me…

00:49:30.322 --> 00:49:34.409
my daughter's engagement is also at stake.

00:49:46.338 --> 00:49:48.673
I will comply with your wishes.

00:49:50.467 --> 00:49:51.718
Good!

00:49:51.802 --> 00:49:52.761
All right!

00:49:53.512 --> 00:49:54.471
It's settled.

00:49:55.055 --> 00:49:56.181
Well done.

00:50:10.529 --> 00:50:11.613
All right then.

00:50:43.395 --> 00:50:44.229
Take a seat.

00:50:49.818 --> 00:50:53.655
We have three hours
until the engagement party.

00:51:03.123 --> 00:51:05.166
{\an8}CONGRATULATIONS ON YOUR ENGAGEMENT

00:51:21.474 --> 00:51:22.601
Hold on.

00:51:24.477 --> 00:51:25.937
Is this someone's 60th birthday party?

00:51:26.521 --> 00:51:27.606
Get rid of anything drab.

00:51:29.107 --> 00:51:30.150
Take it away.

00:51:32.068 --> 00:51:33.528
Welcome, sir.

00:51:33.612 --> 00:51:34.571
Hey.

00:51:36.489 --> 00:51:37.616
Honey.

00:51:40.785 --> 00:51:42.287
Not that way.

00:51:42.370 --> 00:51:43.496
Move it.

00:51:43.580 --> 00:51:45.457
- It's this way.
- Goodness.

00:51:45.540 --> 00:51:49.336
Isn't it better to take
the commemorative shots at the end?

00:51:49.419 --> 00:51:52.631
Come on, this is supposed to be
a cozy family affair.

00:51:52.714 --> 00:51:54.883
- Gosh.
- We should take lots of family shots.

00:52:01.640 --> 00:52:03.058
Smile.

00:52:04.225 --> 00:52:06.102
Look at all this unnecessary fuss.

00:52:06.603 --> 00:52:09.522
Let's make sure yours is a simple,
sophisticated affair.

00:52:10.774 --> 00:52:11.608
Sure.

00:52:13.693 --> 00:52:15.779
We're still missing
the stars of today's show.

00:52:26.247 --> 00:52:29.042
{\an8}CELEBRATING THE ENGAGEMENT
OF SHIN JUNG-WOO AND KANG NORA

00:52:49.104 --> 00:52:50.021
Nora.

00:52:51.648 --> 00:52:52.899
I'm sorry.

00:52:53.483 --> 00:52:56.653
I don't think
I'll be able to make it today.

00:53:02.784 --> 00:53:04.577
Do other people know?

00:53:06.955 --> 00:53:07.831
No.

00:53:13.294 --> 00:53:14.254
Nora!

00:53:15.296 --> 00:53:16.339
Nora!

00:53:16.423 --> 00:53:17.882
Where did she go?

00:53:21.136 --> 00:53:22.554
Oh my. Nora.

00:53:23.763 --> 00:53:24.639
Nora.

00:53:28.018 --> 00:53:30.186
Nora, why did you lock the doors?

00:53:30.270 --> 00:53:32.897
You only have five minutes left.

00:53:32.981 --> 00:53:34.607
Who are you on the phone with?

00:53:35.567 --> 00:53:36.401
Then…

00:53:37.277 --> 00:53:39.029
can you tell them I dumped you?

00:53:40.405 --> 00:53:42.449
Tell them I called off the engagement.

00:53:47.078 --> 00:53:47.996
Nora.

00:54:00.800 --> 00:54:01.843
Why are you crying?

00:54:02.343 --> 00:54:03.261
Nora.

00:54:37.921 --> 00:54:39.464
Something's not right.

00:54:40.465 --> 00:54:41.508
Why aren't they starting?

00:54:43.218 --> 00:54:45.428
Maybe something happened?

00:54:46.888 --> 00:54:48.723
Are they still not here?

00:54:48.807 --> 00:54:50.266
The chairman's there.

00:54:50.350 --> 00:54:51.601
What is going on?

00:54:51.684 --> 00:54:53.186
They're still not here.

00:55:13.790 --> 00:55:14.791
I'm sorry.

00:55:16.835 --> 00:55:18.002
You're sorry?

00:55:18.503 --> 00:55:21.172
President Shin, are you out of your mind?

00:55:21.714 --> 00:55:23.883
How could you humiliate us like this?

00:55:25.260 --> 00:55:26.219
My Nora.

00:55:26.302 --> 00:55:27.971
What are you going to do about my Nora?

00:55:28.054 --> 00:55:29.514
Tell me!

00:55:41.359 --> 00:55:43.111
So, what will you do?

00:55:43.194 --> 00:55:47.157
We can carry on
with the engagement party as planned.

00:55:48.283 --> 00:55:50.326
Both Nora and her mother

00:55:51.077 --> 00:55:53.079
are excited about the princess play,

00:55:53.997 --> 00:55:56.541
so we can't disappoint them.

00:55:57.125 --> 00:55:59.127
A mere scandal of a broken engagement

00:56:00.044 --> 00:56:02.505
will be forgotten over time.

00:56:03.840 --> 00:56:06.050
If you care about Nora as her father,

00:56:07.093 --> 00:56:08.428
you should call it off now.

00:56:09.220 --> 00:56:10.138
Is that so?

00:56:11.973 --> 00:56:13.808
Then let's do that.

00:56:15.185 --> 00:56:17.103
Let's make one thing clear.

00:56:18.188 --> 00:56:19.647
You're the one who called it off.

00:56:20.815 --> 00:56:23.526
I, too, do not wish

00:56:23.610 --> 00:56:27.071
for Nora to think of me
as a heartless father.

00:57:15.370 --> 00:57:16.913
They used to enjoy eating chocolate.

00:57:17.413 --> 00:57:18.539
Bom and Eun-joo, I mean.

00:57:20.208 --> 00:57:21.292
Yeah.

00:57:21.876 --> 00:57:24.879
I used to find it annoying when Ms. Song
called her Ms. Kang with respect,

00:57:24.963 --> 00:57:28.424
and the other assistants
called her a princess.

00:57:28.508 --> 00:57:30.343
But hearing about the arranged marriage,

00:57:30.426 --> 00:57:32.303
it really feels like
she lives in another world.

00:57:33.972 --> 00:57:36.558
But it's also a crucial part
of our next objective.

00:57:39.852 --> 00:57:42.105
If I'm being honest, I do feel bad

00:57:42.188 --> 00:57:44.816
about the hostility I showed her
after I learned who her father was.

00:57:45.817 --> 00:57:48.361
After all, she was also used
to make a borrowed-name account,

00:57:48.444 --> 00:57:49.862
just because she's his daughter.

00:57:50.363 --> 00:57:52.907
There's no reason for her
to participate in this theft,

00:57:53.408 --> 00:57:56.035
especially when her father is the target.

00:58:03.668 --> 00:58:04.502
Hello?

00:58:04.586 --> 00:58:06.588
Aunt Nora and President Shin's engagement
was called off.

00:58:07.672 --> 00:58:09.966
They called off the engagement? Why?

00:58:10.049 --> 00:58:10.883
It's canceled?

00:58:13.511 --> 00:58:15.179
Hey guys.

00:58:23.146 --> 00:58:24.272
What happened to you?

00:58:27.108 --> 00:58:29.819
I fell while climbing over the dorm walls.

00:58:30.320 --> 00:58:32.113
I had nowhere else to go.

00:58:34.157 --> 00:58:35.867
- Come in.
- Come on.

00:58:41.789 --> 00:58:43.291
We'll get you a change of clothes.

00:58:46.085 --> 00:58:47.295
Why did they call it off?

00:58:48.087 --> 00:58:49.047
I'm not sure.

00:58:52.300 --> 00:58:53.134
Oh my god.

00:59:12.612 --> 00:59:13.488
Here.

00:59:17.367 --> 00:59:19.035
What is all that money about?

00:59:21.329 --> 00:59:22.455
You must be thirsty. Here.

00:59:24.415 --> 00:59:25.333
Drink up.

00:59:28.753 --> 00:59:30.004
You remember

00:59:30.088 --> 00:59:32.715
I was awarded the Outstanding Woman
a few months ago, right?

00:59:33.716 --> 00:59:35.259
- Yes.
- Not too long after that,

00:59:35.343 --> 00:59:38.346
twenty-four billion won was deposited
into Hong Jang-mi's account.

00:59:39.389 --> 00:59:41.849
It was Hanmin's secret slush fund.

00:59:43.559 --> 00:59:45.395
So the day I filled in for Ms. Hong,

00:59:45.478 --> 00:59:47.730
you two were busy stealing
that huge amount of money.

00:59:47.814 --> 00:59:48.648
Right?

00:59:49.899 --> 00:59:52.860
Wait, how much is all that?

00:59:53.361 --> 00:59:54.404
It's too much.

00:59:55.279 --> 00:59:57.990
There's even more under your name.

00:59:58.074 --> 01:00:00.034
What? Me? Why?

01:00:00.118 --> 01:00:02.829
I know this is important and all,

01:00:02.912 --> 01:00:04.872
but what happened
with the engagement today?

01:00:07.166 --> 01:00:10.628
If I'm being honest,
I had a feeling this would happen.

01:00:11.754 --> 01:00:16.217
I overheard my father
talking to Ms. Song a few days ago.

01:00:16.676 --> 01:00:18.845
Then they should've postponed it
or canceled the party.

01:00:18.928 --> 01:00:19.846
Why did they proceed?

01:00:22.432 --> 01:00:24.434
That's just the kind of person
my father is.

01:00:25.935 --> 01:00:27.895
Even when I was kidnapped as a kid,

01:00:28.396 --> 01:00:30.565
he refused to pay the ransom

01:00:31.107 --> 01:00:32.608
and gave me up immediately.

01:00:37.363 --> 01:00:40.700
You two can never win against him alone.

01:00:41.451 --> 01:00:44.162
You need the money
hidden under my name too, right?

01:00:48.791 --> 01:00:49.625
That money…

01:00:50.752 --> 01:00:52.587
can be withdrawn by you.

01:00:53.087 --> 01:00:56.507
Just as I withdrew the money
under Hong Jang-mi's name.

01:01:05.183 --> 01:01:09.604
SEOUL CITY DORMITORY
FOR SINGLE FEMALE WORKERS

01:01:11.856 --> 01:01:12.690
Kang Nora!

01:01:12.774 --> 01:01:14.358
I knew you'd be here.

01:01:14.442 --> 01:01:16.486
Seriously, you couldn't go anywhere else?

01:01:16.986 --> 01:01:18.613
You'd better tell me the truth.

01:01:19.155 --> 01:01:20.490
President Shin dumped you, didn't he?

01:01:21.115 --> 01:01:22.700
I dumped him!

01:01:22.784 --> 01:01:24.202
As if!

01:01:24.827 --> 01:01:26.704
That's what he and I agreed upon!

01:01:26.788 --> 01:01:27.747
Who cares?

01:01:27.830 --> 01:01:29.582
We were completely humiliated
for all to see!

01:01:29.665 --> 01:01:30.708
Ma'am.

01:01:30.792 --> 01:01:33.920
Nora must be exhausted,
so you should be gentle with her.

01:01:35.463 --> 01:01:36.714
And who are you?

01:01:38.174 --> 01:01:39.383
She's my friend, Hong Jang-mi.

01:01:39.467 --> 01:01:40.551
I told you about her.

01:01:41.594 --> 01:01:42.428
Right.

01:01:43.513 --> 01:01:45.765
I'm just very much on edge right now.

01:01:46.307 --> 01:01:48.100
Let's go home. Your dad's waiting.

01:01:48.184 --> 01:01:50.061
You must be out of your damn mind. Get in!

01:01:54.398 --> 01:01:55.233
Let's go.

01:02:05.952 --> 01:02:08.830
She's so afraid of defying her father.

01:02:08.913 --> 01:02:10.289
You think she'll accept our offer?

01:02:12.041 --> 01:02:13.417
Maybe we shared too much?

01:02:30.601 --> 01:02:31.602
That money

01:02:31.686 --> 01:02:33.813
can be withdrawn by you.

01:02:34.313 --> 01:02:37.733
Just as I withdrew the money
under Hong Jang-mi's name.

01:02:38.317 --> 01:02:41.320
Where is that money right now?

01:02:43.155 --> 01:02:44.198
In Switzerland.

01:02:49.662 --> 01:02:50.663
And this is

01:02:51.289 --> 01:02:53.666
the evidence
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi

01:02:53.749 --> 01:02:55.835
was going to use
to blow the whistle on Hanmin.

01:02:56.460 --> 01:02:58.754
We believe his accident in July

01:02:58.838 --> 01:03:00.798
wasn't a coincidence.

01:03:04.468 --> 01:03:06.012
- Mom.
- What?

01:03:06.512 --> 01:03:07.889
I want to go on a trip.

01:03:09.307 --> 01:03:10.516
What?

01:03:10.600 --> 01:03:11.851
Where? The US?

01:03:11.934 --> 01:03:13.644
You want to go to the US?

01:03:13.728 --> 01:03:14.562
No.

01:03:15.605 --> 01:03:16.439
Switzerland.

01:03:17.690 --> 01:03:18.524
Switzerland?

01:03:27.617 --> 01:03:28.534
Will President Shin be fired?

01:03:29.118 --> 01:03:30.369
He should be.

01:03:30.453 --> 01:03:31.329
Of course.

01:03:32.455 --> 01:03:35.291
He must've expected as much
when he called off the marriage.

01:03:36.626 --> 01:03:37.710
In the Republic of Korea?

01:03:39.003 --> 01:03:42.882
There's no hard line between
the professional and personal here.

01:03:43.841 --> 01:03:47.136
I have been by the chairman's side
for 26 years now, so I know.

01:03:47.845 --> 01:03:50.514
He's going to tighten
things up internally now.

01:03:50.598 --> 01:03:51.515
That's when

01:03:52.391 --> 01:03:55.186
you push past Nora and rise to the top.

01:03:56.145 --> 01:03:57.480
This is a golden opportunity, okay?

01:03:58.397 --> 01:03:59.231
Okay.

01:04:00.232 --> 01:04:01.192
All right then.

01:04:32.306 --> 01:04:34.558
Where are all the files
that were on my desk?

01:04:34.642 --> 01:04:36.894
The Audit Division took everything.

01:04:37.395 --> 01:04:38.646
The chairman ordered them to.

01:04:41.148 --> 01:04:45.361
Ms. Song said you're free to leave
without saying your farewells.

01:04:54.537 --> 01:04:57.581
Thank you for your hard work.

01:04:58.499 --> 01:04:59.417
Not at all.

01:05:17.143 --> 01:05:19.353
Please take good care of Hong Keum-bo.

01:05:27.862 --> 01:05:30.448
- He hasn't even been here that long.
- I know, right?

01:06:12.073 --> 01:06:14.867
I see Ms. Go is incredibly diligent
about sharing my location.

01:06:14.950 --> 01:06:17.661
Thanks to her, you have
someone to see you off now.

01:06:18.454 --> 01:06:19.830
How does it feel to be fired?

01:06:20.623 --> 01:06:23.501
Being rejected by the organization
you once belonged to…

01:06:24.210 --> 01:06:25.044
It sucks, doesn't it?

01:06:25.127 --> 01:06:30.758
Both Hanmin and DK Ventures
have decided that I am of no use to them.

01:06:30.841 --> 01:06:32.301
It sucks a lot.

01:06:33.219 --> 01:06:35.304
Hong Keum-bo's asking makes it worse.

01:06:38.808 --> 01:06:41.143
Meet me at the street stall
in Yeouido tonight.

01:06:41.977 --> 01:06:42.853
Why?

01:06:42.937 --> 01:06:44.814
Aren't you done with me now that I'm out?

01:07:04.375 --> 01:07:06.043
ELIMINATING CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM'S
INNER CIRCLE

01:07:06.127 --> 01:07:07.294
{\an8}STEP 1: PRESIDENT SHIN JUNG-WOO
ELIMINATED

01:07:15.302 --> 01:07:16.846
JANUARY 1998

01:07:16.929 --> 01:07:18.389
You've reached Song Ju-ran.

01:07:18.472 --> 01:07:19.306
It's Hong Keum-bo.

01:07:20.224 --> 01:07:21.308
You don't even hide it now?

01:07:22.351 --> 01:07:23.561
You need to keep your promise.

01:07:24.436 --> 01:07:25.938
You broke that promise

01:07:26.021 --> 01:07:27.481
when you sent
that crazy burglar to my dorm.

01:07:28.107 --> 01:07:30.067
I sent you a gift,

01:07:30.151 --> 01:07:31.360
so enjoy.

01:07:33.863 --> 01:07:34.738
Come in.

01:07:36.699 --> 01:07:38.117
This came for you, ma'am.

01:07:49.879 --> 01:07:51.839
REPORT ON THE STATUS
OF LARGE SHAREHOLDINGS

01:07:51.922 --> 01:07:54.258
SECTION 1: SUMMARY

01:07:54.758 --> 01:07:57.011
{\an8}HELD BY: YEOUIDO PIRATES
CEO: HONG KEUM-BO

01:08:00.848 --> 01:08:03.475
MARKET PURCHASE OF SHARES (OVER 9%)

01:08:23.621 --> 01:08:25.331
Where is Hong Jang-mi?

01:08:26.040 --> 01:08:27.625
Maybe she's at the IT Division?

01:08:28.876 --> 01:08:29.710
What's this?

01:08:31.420 --> 01:08:33.005
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

01:08:33.088 --> 01:08:34.173
A resignation letter?

01:08:34.256 --> 01:08:35.841
Ms. Hong, this brat…

01:08:36.508 --> 01:08:37.593
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

01:08:37.676 --> 01:08:39.678
Is this company a joke to her?

01:09:06.455 --> 01:09:07.581
Hong Keum-bo.

01:09:09.458 --> 01:09:12.127
I confirmed that the FSS
processed her resignation.

01:09:14.505 --> 01:09:15.464
Hong Keum-bo,

01:09:16.548 --> 01:09:18.008
under the Yeouido Pirates' name,

01:09:18.884 --> 01:09:21.428
managed to buy up 9% of Hanmin's stocks.

01:09:24.056 --> 01:09:26.267
She dared to buy
our stocks with that money?

01:09:27.643 --> 01:09:28.644
Damn.

01:09:29.478 --> 01:09:30.562
I mean,

01:09:31.855 --> 01:09:34.275
she could've lived out her whole life
with that money.

01:09:34.358 --> 01:09:36.568
Why go through the trouble?
What's the point?

01:09:38.904 --> 01:09:40.197
What matters is

01:09:40.948 --> 01:09:43.284
that the chairman's slush fund is gone.

01:09:44.410 --> 01:09:46.412
Listen, we can just retrieve

01:09:46.996 --> 01:09:49.206
the money that was stolen, all right?

01:09:49.290 --> 01:09:51.208
If we crack down hard--

01:09:51.292 --> 01:09:52.126
No.

01:09:53.127 --> 01:09:54.545
Don't act rashly.

01:09:55.462 --> 01:09:56.880
The risk is too high.

01:09:58.132 --> 01:10:01.176
Tail Hong Keum-bo and keep me updated
on her whereabouts and who she meets.

01:10:02.970 --> 01:10:05.931
I need to figure out
how many insiders are involved first.

01:10:18.360 --> 01:10:19.361
Have a good night.

01:10:25.868 --> 01:10:27.494
Ma'am, a bottle of soju please.

01:10:27.578 --> 01:10:28.412
All right.

01:10:34.335 --> 01:10:35.169
Here you go.

01:10:38.630 --> 01:10:40.007
Look at you waiting patiently.

01:10:40.090 --> 01:10:43.218
Are you dressed like that because you're
no longer afraid of getting caught?

01:10:44.094 --> 01:10:46.388
I've never stopped being me.

01:10:46.472 --> 01:10:50.059
I used Song Ju-ran
to drive out President Shin Jung-woo.

01:10:50.142 --> 01:10:51.685
I thought as much.

01:10:52.186 --> 01:10:53.562
Congratulations on the achievement.

01:10:53.645 --> 01:10:56.440
And now I need an M&A expert
who can help me

01:10:56.523 --> 01:10:58.359
secure management control.

01:11:09.203 --> 01:11:11.789
REPORT ON THE STATUS
OF LARGE SHAREHOLDINGS

01:11:12.373 --> 01:11:13.749
Yeouido Pirates?

01:11:13.832 --> 01:11:16.001
I'm trying to recruit you right now,
Shin Jung-woo.

01:11:17.503 --> 01:11:19.380
Join Yeouido Pirates.

01:11:32.476 --> 01:11:36.355
{\an8}SPECIAL THANKS TO SHIN YU-NA
FOR HER APPEARANCE

01:12:07.594 --> 01:12:09.430
{\an8}UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

01:12:10.097 --> 01:12:11.807
{\an8}Yeouido Pirates is back.

01:12:12.474 --> 01:12:13.809
{\an8}I will appoint

01:12:13.892 --> 01:12:16.603
{\an8}whoever catches the Captain first

01:12:16.687 --> 01:12:18.397
{\an8}as the president.

01:12:18.480 --> 01:12:19.857
{\an8}It must be a coincidence.

01:12:19.940 --> 01:12:22.526
{\an8}Only the chairman and I know
about that Swiss account.

01:12:22.609 --> 01:12:24.736
{\an8}Kang Nora is in Switzerland right now.

01:12:24.820 --> 01:12:27.239
{\an8}How are you so sure
that Kang Nora will take your side?

01:12:27.823 --> 01:12:28.991
{\an8}Ms. Song's safe.

01:12:29.074 --> 01:12:30.534
{\an8}That's the gold mine.

01:12:30.617 --> 01:12:33.620
{\an8}Is Hanmin surrounded by hostile forces,

01:12:33.704 --> 01:12:35.497
{\an8}just waiting to strike?

01:12:35.581 --> 01:12:37.291
{\an8}The Captain of Yeouido Pirates.

01:12:37.374 --> 01:12:38.333
{\an8}I know who it is.

01:12:40.794 --> 01:12:45.799
{\an8}Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim